1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,689
Every day, it seems, this takes place in the fast-moving world of business.

2
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:10,369
The boss calls in an employee and explains that a special task must be accomplished.

3
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:15,490
Then he says, I know you got a lot of work to do, but can you handle this?

4
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:21,409
Too often the employee replies, I'm awfully sorry, but I'm all loaded down now.

5
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:24,850
I wish I could take it on, but I'm just too busy.

6
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:33,330
Under the circumstances, the boss doesn't hold it against the employee because it is extra duty, so to speak.

7
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:42,369
But the boss realizes the task must be done, and he'll keep on looking until he finds an employee who is just as busy as the rest,

8
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,929
but who feels he can take on more.

9
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:48,929
And this employee is the fellow who will forge ahead.

10
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:56,450
In business, in the home, in the community, the success combination is do what you do better,

11
00:00:56,560 --> 00:01:00,850
improve the quality of your output, and do more of what you do,

12
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,250
increase the quantity of your output.

13
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:06,929
Convinced it pays to do more and better?

14
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:09,490
Then try this two-step procedure.

15
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:11,169
1.

16
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,610
Eagerly accept the opportunity to do more.

17
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:18,210
It's a compliment to be asked to take on a new responsibility.

18
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:24,369
Accepting greater responsibility on the job makes you stand out and shows that you're more valuable.

19
00:01:24,639 --> 00:01:29,169
When your neighbors ask you to represent them on a civic matter, accept.

20
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:32,210
It helps you to become a community leader.

21
00:01:32,210 --> 00:01:33,649
2.

22
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:37,250
Next, concentrate on how can I do more?

23
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,409
Creative answers will come.

24
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,010
Some of these answers may be better planning and organization of your present work,

25
00:01:45,119 --> 00:01:52,929
or taking intelligent shortcuts in your routine activities, or possibly dropping non-essential activities altogether.

26
00:01:53,119 --> 00:01:58,210
But let me repeat, the solution for doing more will appear.

27
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:05,970
As a personal policy, I have accepted fully the concept, if you want it done,

28
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,810
give it to a busy man.

29
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:13,330
I refuse to work on important projects with persons who have lots of free time.

30
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:21,490
I have learned from painful, expensive experience that the fellow who has plenty of time makes an ineffective work partner.

31
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:26,050
All the successful, competent people I know are busy.

32
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:32,530
When I start something, some project with them, I know it will be satisfactorily completed.

33
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:38,290
I have learned in dozens of instances that I can count on a busy man to deliver,

34
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:44,369
but I have often been disappointed in working with people who have all the time in the world.

35
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:50,850
Progressive business management constantly asks, what can we do to expand output?

36
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:55,730
Why not ask yourself, what can I do to expand my output?

37
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,090
Your mind will creatively show you how.

